# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CodeInsight AI — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HOW TO USE
#   • Local dev:  copy this file to `.env` and fill in real values.
#       Windows cmd:  copy .env.example .env
#       PowerShell:   Copy-Item .env.example .env
#       macOS/Linux:  cp .env.example .env
#   • Vercel:     set the same variables in Project → Settings →
#                 Environment Variables (do NOT commit `.env`).
#
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT uses SQLite (file-based, zero external deps).
# VERCEL DEPLOYMENT uses PostgreSQL (Neon, Vercel Postgres, etc.).
# See DEPLOY.md for the full deployment walkthrough.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# DATABASE (required)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# LOCAL: SQLite — Prisma creates the file on first `bun run db:push`.
#   The db/ directory is git-ignored, data stays on your machine only.
DATABASE_URL="file:./db/local.db"
#
# VERCEL (PostgreSQL): override on Vercel → Settings → Env Vars with
# your Neon / Vercel Postgres connection string, e.g.:
#   DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@ep-xxx.REGION.aws.neon.tech/DBNAME?sslmode=require"
#
# NOTE: When deploying to Vercel, set PRISMA_SCHEMA=prisma/schema.prod.prisma
# so the build uses the PostgreSQL schema instead of this SQLite one.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# NEXTAUTH (required)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Random secret used to sign session JWTs.
# Generate one locally with:  openssl rand -base64 32
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="replace-with-a-long-random-string"

# Public URL of the app.
#   Local dev:  http://localhost:3000
#   Vercel:     https://your-project.vercel.app
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# GITHUB OAuth (optional — only needed to analyze PRIVATE repos)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Create at: https://github.com/settings/developers
# Authorization callback URL:
#   Local:  http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/github
#   Vercel: https://your-project.vercel.app/api/auth/callback/github
GITHUB_ID=""
GITHUB_SECRET=""

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# GOOGLE OAuth (optional)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Create at: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# Authorized redirect URI:
#   Local:  http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/google
#   Vercel: https://your-project.vercel.app/api/auth/callback/google
GOOGLE_ID=""
GOOGLE_SECRET=""

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOTES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# • OAuth is OPTIONAL. The app fully works on public repos + AI
#   provider keys configured in the UI (Settings → AI Providers).
#   OAuth is only required to analyze your PRIVATE GitHub repos.
# • AI provider API keys (OpenAI, OpenRouter, Anthropic, …) are
#   NOT stored here — they are entered in the app UI and kept in
#   the browser only.
